-- Top Citigroup lawyer for global consumer business leaves bank
-- By David Henry in New York
-- Tue Aug 19, 2014 05:31PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 19 (Reuters) - Citigroup Inc's <C.N> general counsel for its global consumer business, Stephen Simcock, is leaving the bank "to pursue another opportunity," a spokeswoman said on Tuesday.

Anita Romero, formerly head the corporate legal department, will replace Simcock and will continue to hold her current post as general counsel of Citibank N.A., the company's primary subsidiary, spokeswoman Elizabeth Fogerty said by email.